  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Towards future perspectives on wastewater treatment and sustainable sludge management based on LCA methodology in the context of climate change and the water-energy-food nexus</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to give follow-up to the recommendations given in the Strategic vision on Sludge to Energy, support is needed on:1. The development of nation-wide strategies for evaluating the impacts and implications of climate change on wastewater treatment and sustainable sludge management in the context of the water-energy-food nexus. To reach this objective, the environmental performance based on LCA methodology of different scenarios for the improvement of existing WWTPs and sludge management will be studied, including paying attention to the cost-effectiveness of each proposed scenario.2. The development of real business cases/models based on the results of the LCA methodology for both sewage treatment and sludge management improvement. This will help decision-makers to develop future plans. More importantly, it could provide a basis to attract the attention of the private sector to invest in this important sector.</narrative>
  </description>
